## Time Stop Overshoot (±5 min) — NOT A BUG, CLOSE

With a missing bar, the code exits at the close of the first available bar after
the 60-minute threshold. A 65-minute exit means the bar at minute 60 was missing and
the next bar is at minute 65. This is the only correct behavior in a bar-driven
backtester — you cannot exit at a bar that does not exist. The 5-minute overshoot
equals one bar interval and is irreducible without tick data.

This is assumption drift (the TIME_STOP_MINUTES spec assumes continuous bars), not
a code error. Document it; do not fix it.

